What about the teachers?

264
00:17:18.676 --> 00:17:21.095
Any rotten apples there?

265
00:17:21.179 --> 00:17:23.306
I don't know.

266
00:17:26.476 --> 00:17:29.645
MARY:
So now begins the great trek


267
00:17:29.729 --> 00:17:31.981
of 1836.

268
00:17:32.064 --> 00:17:34.317
The white boys
are looking north.


269
00:17:34.400 --> 00:17:35.818
They say,
"what do you see?"


270
00:17:35.902 --> 00:17:39.071
"We see great land, men,
beautiful land!"


271
00:17:39.155 --> 00:17:40.323
"Anybody there?"

272
00:17:40.406 --> 00:17:43.076
"No. Just a few gaffers

273
00:17:43.159 --> 00:17:45.995
sticking spears up
each other's future."


274
00:17:46.078 --> 00:17:47.997
"So, what do you say
we make a trek?"


275
00:17:48.080 --> 00:17:49.373
"Good idea."

276
00:17:49.457 --> 00:17:52.794
And what does this
bring to us?


277
00:17:52.877 --> 00:17:54.045
Shambucks,

278
00:17:54.128 --> 00:17:55.797
passbooks,

279
00:17:55.880 --> 00:17:57.465
P.W. Botha.

280
00:17:57.548 --> 00:18:00.092
Afrikaans lessons, and--

281
00:18:02.929 --> 00:18:05.807
And democracy and justice

282
00:18:05.890 --> 00:18:08.726
and very, very,
very fine schools, yes.


283
00:18:08.810 --> 00:18:10.728
( laughs )
We're so lucky!


284
00:18:10.812 --> 00:18:12.313
Isn't history beautiful?

285
00:18:12.396 --> 00:18:14.690
ALL ( in unison ):
Yeah!


286
00:18:14.774 --> 00:18:17.985
( chattering )

287
00:18:34.752 --> 00:18:37.171
( indistinct chatter )

288
00:18:37.255 --> 00:18:40.216
SARAFINA:
<i>There's this boy</i>
<i>who wants to go out with me.</i>


289
00:18:40.299 --> 00:18:42.051
<i>His name is Crocodile.</i>

290
00:18:42.134 --> 00:18:45.137
<i>He thinks he's great.</i>
<i>But I like him--</i>


291
00:18:45.221 --> 00:18:47.557
<i>Except he burns down schools.</i>

292
00:18:47.640 --> 00:18:49.725
<i>What's the future in that?</i>

293
00:18:49.809 --> 00:18:51.435
<i>He'll take me to the movies,</i>

294
00:18:51.519 --> 00:18:54.772
<i>and then he'll be</i>
<i>in prison for 20 years.</i>


295
00:18:57.316 --> 00:18:58.901
You don't
go in store.


296
00:18:58.985 --> 00:19:00.444
You stay outside.

297
00:19:00.528 --> 00:19:02.029
You don't hurt anybody.

298
00:19:02.113 --> 00:19:03.573
We hurt
the Boers' business.


299
00:19:03.656 --> 00:19:05.241
Hey! Burn the store.

300
00:19:05.324 --> 00:19:07.368
You want to hurt the Boers'
business, burn it down!


301
00:19:07.451 --> 00:19:09.704
It takes one man
to burn a store.


302
00:19:09.787 --> 00:19:12.206
It takes a thousand
to close it down.


303
00:19:12.290 --> 00:19:13.749
We need thousands!

304
00:19:13.833 --> 00:19:16.252
We want the people awake,
alive, angry!


305
00:19:16.335 --> 00:19:17.753
That's it!

306
00:19:17.837 --> 00:19:19.714
They don't want angry,
they want quiet!


307
00:19:19.797 --> 00:19:20.923
Mama goes to church,

308
00:19:21.007 --> 00:19:22.258
Papa goes to the<i>shebeen,</i>

309
00:19:22.341 --> 00:19:23.551
the kids play
in the streets!


310
00:19:23.634 --> 00:19:24.927
Burn it down!

311
00:19:25.011 --> 00:19:26.721
They're not going to
get a quiet life


312
00:19:26.804 --> 00:19:28.306
so long as I'm around.

313
00:19:28.389 --> 00:19:31.100
( overlapping talking )

314
00:19:31.183 --> 00:19:33.769
I'm asking you

315
00:19:33.853 --> 00:19:36.939
to help me...

316
00:19:37.023 --> 00:19:40.234
for the sake
of the children.


317
00:19:40.318 --> 00:19:42.945
All it takes is
a few troublemakers,


318
00:19:43.029 --> 00:19:44.780
but they all pay the price,

319
00:19:44.864 --> 00:19:47.283
all of them.

320
00:19:47.366 --> 00:19:49.285
So I want you to help me

321
00:19:49.368 --> 00:19:51.787
to identify
these troublemakers.


322
00:20:00.171 --> 00:20:02.131
What is this silence?

323
00:20:02.214 --> 00:20:04.175
What does it mean, huh?

324
00:20:04.258 --> 00:20:07.762
That you don't believe that
there are any troublemakers?


325
00:20:07.845 --> 00:20:11.182
Or that you don't
want to help me, huh?


326
00:20:11.265 --> 00:20:12.683
Huh?

327
00:20:12.767 --> 00:20:14.977
You want us to tell you
who firebombed the wall.


328
00:20:15.061 --> 00:20:16.479
We don't know that.

329
00:20:16.562 --> 00:20:18.773
Maybe you know
some kids with bad attitudes


330
00:20:18.856 --> 00:20:20.149
cursing the soldiers,

331
00:20:20.232 --> 00:20:21.442
shouting, "viva Mandela!"

332
00:20:21.525 --> 00:20:23.527
Sure.

333
00:20:23.611 --> 00:20:25.321
So tell me.

334
00:20:25.404 --> 00:20:28.115
All of them.

335
00:20:28.199 --> 00:20:29.575
That's funny.

336
00:20:29.659 --> 00:20:31.494
That's really funny, lady.

337
00:20:31.577 --> 00:20:33.996
Maybe there's some teachers
with bad attitudes,


338
00:20:34.080 --> 00:20:35.998
teachers who teach
children to hate


339
00:20:36.082 --> 00:20:37.959
and burn and kill.

340
00:20:38.042 --> 00:20:40.002
To me, that is
worse than murder.


341
00:20:40.086 --> 00:20:42.672
That is killing
a child's soul.


342
00:20:42.755 --> 00:20:44.632
None of my staff
teach violence.


343
00:20:44.715 --> 00:20:46.300
That is not enough!

344
00:20:46.384 --> 00:20:49.178
Not for teachers who are
responsible for young minds.


345
00:20:49.261 --> 00:20:50.513
They have to
reject violence.


346
00:20:50.596 --> 00:20:51.931
They have to
hate violence!


347
00:20:52.014 --> 00:20:53.349
They have to tear it
out by the roots!


348
00:20:56.978 --> 00:20:59.522
We know there are people behind
this trouble in the schools,


349
00:20:59.605 --> 00:21:01.357
and we know
where to look,


350
00:21:01.440 --> 00:21:02.984
and believe me--
Believe me,


351
00:21:03.067 --> 00:21:05.778
we're looking.

352
00:21:17.289 --> 00:21:19.417
( singing in
South African language )


353
00:21:43.315 --> 00:21:46.819
Quiet, quiet, quiet!
I'm here!


354
00:21:46.902 --> 00:21:48.571
Better late than never.

355
00:21:48.654 --> 00:21:50.031
Sarafina, Crocodile.

356
00:21:50.114 --> 00:21:51.866
Here today
is the plan, people.


357
00:21:51.949 --> 00:21:53.284
You will do all the work,

358
00:21:53.367 --> 00:21:55.786
and I go to sleep.

359
00:21:55.870 --> 00:21:57.621
Have we got it
all worked out then?


360
00:21:57.705 --> 00:21:59.874
ALL:
Yes!


361
00:21:59.957 --> 00:22:01.584
Who needs a show?

362
00:22:01.667 --> 00:22:04.503
I sing a song,
everybody watches me.


363
00:22:04.587 --> 00:22:05.755
Song about what?

364
00:22:05.838 --> 00:22:07.256
SARAFINA:
About me! What else?


365
00:22:07.339 --> 00:22:09.383
MARY:
We have six weeks.


366
00:22:09.467 --> 00:22:11.260
Let's move it.

367
00:22:11.343 --> 00:22:13.095
Hey! Train song!
Stimela says!


368
00:22:13.179 --> 00:22:14.430
( cheering )

369
00:22:14.513 --> 00:22:16.599
( singing in
South African language )


370
00:22:16.682 --> 00:22:20.102
( laughter and drumming )

371
00:22:20.186 --> 00:22:21.771
♪ This is the night
For you and me ♪


372
00:22:21.854 --> 00:22:23.606
♪ Aiy yo yo yo ♪

373
00:22:21.854 --> 00:22:23.606
Hmm.

374
00:22:23.689 --> 00:22:26.192
And just where is
this train going?


375
00:22:26.275 --> 00:22:27.777
Just going, mistress.

376
00:22:27.860 --> 00:22:29.737
At 4:00 in the morning,

377
00:22:29.820 --> 00:22:31.906
Stimela takes the men
from their loved ones,


378
00:22:31.989 --> 00:22:33.282
and at 6 in the evening,

379
00:22:33.365 --> 00:22:35.117
the children are
waiting for Stimela


380
00:22:35.201 --> 00:22:36.952
to bring back their
fathers and mothers.


381
00:22:37.036 --> 00:22:38.287
Stimela says so.

382
00:22:38.370 --> 00:22:42.541
Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh.
Yes, I see. Hmm.


383
00:22:42.625 --> 00:22:44.835
So they come back?

384
00:22:42.625 --> 00:22:44.835
Sure, they come back.

385
00:22:44.919 --> 00:22:46.962
A happy ending.
I like that.


386
00:22:47.046 --> 00:22:48.422
ALL:
Mm-hmm.


387
00:22:48.506 --> 00:22:50.299
I love happy endings.

388
00:22:50.382 --> 00:22:52.093
You think of
a happy ending,


389
00:22:52.176 --> 00:22:53.761
and you've got a show.

390
00:22:53.844 --> 00:22:55.763
BOY 1:
Here's the story
with a happy ending!


391
00:22:55.846 --> 00:22:58.974
Killer disease
comes to South Africa,


392
00:22:59.058 --> 00:23:00.851
but only the Boers get it.

393
00:23:00.935 --> 00:23:02.770
( laughter )

394
00:23:02.853 --> 00:23:05.523
BOY 2:
Mistress! Mistress! Gold!


395
00:23:05.606 --> 00:23:08.776
We strike gold in Soweto,
and we all get rich!


396
00:23:08.859 --> 00:23:10.528
Jesus comes back!

397
00:23:10.611 --> 00:23:13.155
( laughter )

398
00:23:13.239 --> 00:23:14.698
Bah bah bah!

399
00:23:14.782 --> 00:23:16.325
( laughter )

400
00:23:16.408 --> 00:23:18.035
Mandela comes back!

401
00:23:18.119 --> 00:23:20.621
Yes!

402
00:23:18.119 --> 00:23:20.621
( cheering )

403
00:23:20.704 --> 00:23:23.833
MARY:
Yes! Yes, yes, yes, yes!


404
00:23:23.916 --> 00:23:26.127
Day of liberation.

405
00:23:26.210 --> 00:23:29.296
Mandela comes home
from prison.


406
00:23:29.380 --> 00:23:31.340
I like that. I like it.

407
00:23:31.423 --> 00:23:32.716
I play Nelson Mandela!

408
00:23:32.800 --> 00:23:34.677
The speaker
of the nation!


409
00:23:34.760 --> 00:23:36.345
Why you?

410
00:23:36.428 --> 00:23:37.805
Because I'm a man.

411
00:23:37.888 --> 00:23:40.516
Okay. You want to know
who plays Mandela?


412
00:23:40.599 --> 00:23:42.017
Hmm?

413
00:23:40.599 --> 00:23:42.017
I play Mandela.

414
00:23:42.101 --> 00:23:43.978
You are a girl.

415
00:23:42.101 --> 00:23:43.978
So what?!

416
00:23:44.061 --> 00:23:45.396
MARY:
Sarafina,


417
00:23:45.479 --> 00:23:49.024
tell us what happens
in your story, hmm?


418
00:23:49.108 --> 00:23:53.028
The day Nelson Mandela
walks free,


419
00:23:53.112 --> 00:23:56.574
all the crowds, everyone
laughing and singing.


420
00:23:56.657 --> 00:23:58.659
Yes, Sarafina!

421
00:23:58.742 --> 00:24:02.371
♪ Free at last ♪

422
00:24:02.454 --> 00:24:05.040
♪ Nelson Mandela ♪

423
00:24:05.124 --> 00:24:08.460
♪ Walking down
The street of Soweto ♪


424
00:24:08.544 --> 00:24:10.921
Yes! You got it!

425
00:24:11.005 --> 00:24:13.299
And he speaks
to the people.


426
00:24:13.382 --> 00:24:16.218
Free at last!
Nelson Mandela!


427
00:24:16.302 --> 00:24:19.763
( cheering )

428
00:24:16.302 --> 00:24:19.763
Yes! Yes! Yes!

429
00:24:23.309 --> 00:24:25.811
Yeah!

430
00:24:28.314 --> 00:24:30.858
SARAFINA:
<i>Why can't I be you, Nelson,</i>


431
00:24:30.941 --> 00:24:33.068
<i>just for the school concert,</i>

432
00:24:33.152 --> 00:24:35.738
<i>just once make a big speech</i>

433
00:24:35.821 --> 00:24:37.406
<i>just the way you do it?</i>

434
00:24:37.489 --> 00:24:39.200
<i>Mandela free at last,</i>

435
00:24:39.283 --> 00:24:41.744
<i>everybody clapping</i>
<i>and cheering.</i>


436
00:24:41.827 --> 00:24:44.246
<i>Mandela's free</i>
<i>and I'm the star,</i>


437
00:24:44.330 --> 00:24:46.874
<i>just for a day.</i>
<i>Okay, Nelson?</i>


438
00:24:46.957 --> 00:24:49.210
<i>Your day will come.</i>

439
00:24:51.837 --> 00:24:53.589
MARY:
Hey, Sarafina.


440
00:24:53.672 --> 00:24:55.758
Are you all right,
mistress?


441
00:24:55.841 --> 00:24:57.468
No, but what else is new?

442
00:24:57.551 --> 00:25:01.013
It'll be all right
in heaven, as they say.


443
00:25:01.096 --> 00:25:03.474
Is there anything
I can do?


444
00:25:03.557 --> 00:25:06.268
Just stay as beautiful
as you are.


445
00:25:06.352 --> 00:25:09.521
You know, I liked
your idea for the show.


446
00:25:09.605 --> 00:25:11.941
Mandela free.

447
00:25:12.024 --> 00:25:14.944
It would make a great show,

448
00:25:15.027 --> 00:25:17.029
only...

449
00:25:18.364 --> 00:25:21.909
Only they won't like it.

450
00:25:21.992 --> 00:25:24.495
No, they won't.

451
00:25:24.578 --> 00:25:27.289
So you're saying
we shouldn't do it?


452
00:25:27.373 --> 00:25:30.000
I'm saying
it'll make trouble,


453
00:25:30.084 --> 00:25:32.753
and right now they're
looking for the troublemakers.


454
00:25:32.836 --> 00:25:35.965
I know who the
troublemakers are, mistress.


455
00:25:36.048 --> 00:25:38.509
They get special training
how to kill.


456
00:25:38.592 --> 00:25:41.262
They have guns. 
I've seen them.

457
00:25:38.592 --> 00:25:41.262
Shh!

458
00:25:41.345 --> 00:25:42.471
( men talking outside )

459
00:25:42.554 --> 00:25:44.014
There's two of them.

460
00:25:46.767 --> 00:25:49.019
( Mary exhales )

461
00:25:50.229 --> 00:25:51.480
( laughs )

462
00:25:51.563 --> 00:25:53.774
( laughs )

463
00:25:53.857 --> 00:25:55.985
Hmm.

464
00:26:05.411 --> 00:26:08.289
The Boers want
everything quiet, right?


465
00:26:08.372 --> 00:26:11.292
Everything under control.

466
00:26:11.375 --> 00:26:14.169
Look! The keffeirs are quiet.

467
00:26:14.253 --> 00:26:17.298
A quiet keffeir
is a happy keffeir, man.


468
00:26:17.381 --> 00:26:19.216
But we are not happy,

469
00:26:19.300 --> 00:26:21.093
and we are not quiet,

470
00:26:21.176 --> 00:26:23.929
and we are not under control.

471
00:26:24.013 --> 00:26:26.849
So somebody
better tell the Boers.


472
00:26:26.932 --> 00:26:29.560
People don't like
the boycott of the Boer stores.


473
00:26:29.643 --> 00:26:31.729
They say we only
hurt ourselves.


474
00:26:31.812 --> 00:26:33.731
People say? What people?

475
00:26:33.814 --> 00:26:35.357
People say, "do nothing."

476
00:26:35.441 --> 00:26:37.526
People say,
"what can we do?"


477
00:26:37.609 --> 00:26:41.113
People say, "please,
Mr. Boer, beat me again."


478
00:26:41.196 --> 00:26:44.491
I say, bullshit.
I say, fight!


479
00:26:44.575 --> 00:26:46.869
( overlapping talking )

480
00:26:46.952 --> 00:26:50.164
Okay, sure, fight,
but don't fight the school!


481
00:26:50.247 --> 00:26:51.540
What's the use of that?

482
00:26:51.623 --> 00:26:55.544
The great school.
The wonderful school.


483
00:26:55.627 --> 00:26:58.714
You think they put us
here for education?


484
00:26:58.797 --> 00:27:00.716
This isn't education.

485
00:27:00.799 --> 00:27:03.677
This is some way to
keep us off the streets.


486
00:27:03.761 --> 00:27:05.763
Miss Masembuko
gives us education.


487
00:27:05.846 --> 00:27:07.723
How long
do you give her?


488
00:27:07.806 --> 00:27:09.058
What do you mean?

489
00:27:09.141 --> 00:27:11.560
Open your eyes, Sarafina.

490
00:27:11.643 --> 00:27:13.562
People disappear.

491
00:27:13.645 --> 00:27:15.147
Haven't you noticed?

492
00:27:15.230 --> 00:27:18.233
Mary Masembuko's
one crazy teacher.


493
00:27:18.317 --> 00:27:20.069
How long will they
let her alone


494
00:27:20.152 --> 00:27:22.738
to corrupt
our innocent minds?


495
00:27:22.821 --> 00:27:25.032
( overlapping talking )

496
00:27:29.244 --> 00:27:31.038
Sarafina,
I'll pick you up


497
00:27:31.121 --> 00:27:32.247
at your house later,
okay?


498
00:27:32.331 --> 00:27:33.540
What am I, your<i>pasah?</i>

499
00:27:33.624 --> 00:27:35.250
You're my girl!

500
00:27:33.624 --> 00:27:35.250
Uh-uh.

501
00:27:35.334 --> 00:27:37.044
What is it that
she wants, China?


502
00:27:37.127 --> 00:27:38.754
( speaking
native language )


503
00:27:38.837 --> 00:27:40.422
Maybe she's waiting
for Michael Jackson.


504
00:27:40.506 --> 00:27:42.383
I'm going to Pac Town
to see my mother.


505
00:27:42.466 --> 00:27:44.218
So? You coming back.

506
00:27:44.301 --> 00:27:45.594
Today it's
your lucky day!


507
00:27:45.677 --> 00:27:48.555
Treat yourself.

508
00:27:48.639 --> 00:27:50.891
You really do love yourself,
don't you, Croc?


509
00:27:50.974 --> 00:27:52.476
Sure, I do.
Why not?


510
00:27:52.559 --> 00:27:54.603
There's so much
to love, baby.


511
00:27:54.686 --> 00:27:58.440
So I'll come around
your house later, okay?


512
00:27:58.524 --> 00:28:00.484
You know, he's such
a jerk, that one,


513
00:28:00.567 --> 00:28:02.236
I almost like him.

514
00:28:02.319 --> 00:28:04.238
What is it that
you want, Sarafina?


515
00:28:04.321 --> 00:28:07.157
China,
you know how it is.


516
00:28:07.241 --> 00:28:09.576
I want more.

517
00:28:07.241 --> 00:28:09.576
More what?

518
00:28:09.660 --> 00:28:11.787
More than this.

519
00:28:15.916 --> 00:28:18.877
( muffled announcement
over P.A. System )


520
00:28:28.887 --> 00:28:30.848
This store
is owned by Boers.


521
00:28:32.391 --> 00:28:34.184
We have to support
each other!


522
00:28:35.936 --> 00:28:38.480
Don't give your money
to the Boers.


523
00:28:38.564 --> 00:28:41.150
There's no law that says
you have to show up here.


524
00:28:41.233 --> 00:28:44.153
( rumbles )

525
00:28:41.233 --> 00:28:44.153
( brakes screech )

526
00:28:44.236 --> 00:28:45.654
Boycott the Boers!

527
00:28:45.737 --> 00:28:47.990
( overlapping yelling,
singing, and shouting )


528
00:28:50.075 --> 00:28:52.870
Hey! Hey! Shut up!

529
00:28:52.953 --> 00:28:54.663
You go home.

530
00:28:54.746 --> 00:28:57.583
What's all this fooling
with other people's business?


531
00:28:57.666 --> 00:28:58.959
Why do you show up here,
Mama?


532
00:28:59.042 --> 00:29:00.502
Because I want to,

533
00:29:00.586 --> 00:29:02.463
and I'm not your mama.
Now, out of my way!


534
00:29:02.546 --> 00:29:04.673
You want to give
your money to the Boers?


535
00:29:04.756 --> 00:29:06.467
You want to help them
and not your own people?


536
00:29:06.550 --> 00:29:07.885
You get out of my way!

537
00:29:07.968 --> 00:29:09.678
You boys don't help no one!

538
00:29:09.761 --> 00:29:11.346
All you do is
make things bad!


539
00:29:11.430 --> 00:29:12.890
What's your daddy doing,

540
00:29:12.973 --> 00:29:14.391
letting you run wild
like this?


541
00:29:14.475 --> 00:29:16.810
My daddy is doing
the same as you: nothing!


542
00:29:16.894 --> 00:29:18.353
That's right!

543
00:29:18.437 --> 00:29:19.813
That's why nothing changes,
mama!


544
00:29:21.106 --> 00:29:23.442
Leave my sugar!
Leave my sugar!


545
00:29:23.525 --> 00:29:25.694
( rumbling )

546
00:29:27.112 --> 00:29:28.864
( indistinct talking )

547
00:29:28.947 --> 00:29:31.408
SARAFINA:
<i>I want to tell you something,</i>
<i>Nelson,</i>


548
00:29:31.492 --> 00:29:33.744
<i>I can't tell anyone else.</i>

549
00:29:33.827 --> 00:29:36.205
<i>Whenever I go</i>
<i>to visit my mother,</i>


550
00:29:36.288 --> 00:29:38.999
<i>I feel like I'm visiting</i>
<i>another world</i>


551
00:29:39.082 --> 00:29:41.084
<i>and that I don't</i>
<i>belong there.</i>


552
00:29:41.168 --> 00:29:43.253
<i>That's a bad feeling, right?</i>

553
00:29:43.337 --> 00:29:45.839
<i>I feel like I belong</i>
<i>somewhere else,</i>


554
00:29:45.923 --> 00:29:48.467
<i>somewhere</i>
<i>I've not even seen yet,</i>


555
00:29:48.550 --> 00:29:50.886
<i>but I'll know it</i>
<i>when I see it.</i>


556
00:29:50.969 --> 00:29:53.096
( siren wailing )

557
00:29:56.058 --> 00:29:59.394
( yelling and screaming )

558
00:30:26.380 --> 00:30:28.924
<i>This other world</i>
<i>is called Pac Town.</i>


559
00:30:29.007 --> 00:30:31.760
<i>They keep the streets</i>
<i>very clean in Pac Town.</i>


560
00:30:31.843 --> 00:30:34.221
<i>Mama lives</i>
<i>in a big white house.</i>


561
00:30:34.304 --> 00:30:37.015
<i>Well, in a small room</i>
<i>in the back, really.</i>


562
00:30:37.099 --> 00:30:38.976
<i>But they treat her well.</i>

563
00:30:39.059 --> 00:30:43.021
<i>They say, "oh, Angelina's</i>
<i>just like one of the family."</i>


564
00:30:43.105 --> 00:30:45.274
<i>"The children just love her.</i>

565
00:30:45.357 --> 00:30:48.110
<i>You know how good these</i>
<i>black women are with children."</i>


566
00:30:48.193 --> 00:30:49.444
<i>They're right.</i>

567
00:30:49.528 --> 00:30:51.446
<i>Mama is good with children.</i>

568
00:30:51.530 --> 00:30:54.616
<i>Only her children</i>
<i>don't live here, do they?</i>


569
00:30:54.700 --> 00:30:56.201
Hello.

570
00:30:54.700 --> 00:30:56.201
Hi.

571
00:30:56.285 --> 00:30:57.452
How are you?

572
00:30:56.285 --> 00:30:57.452
I'm fine.

573
00:30:57.536 --> 00:30:59.329
Good.

574
00:31:13.844 --> 00:31:16.138
( humming )

575
00:31:22.394 --> 00:31:25.147
Mama.

576
00:31:25.230 --> 00:31:28.108
Sarafina.

577
00:31:32.529 --> 00:31:34.156
How are my babies?

578
00:31:34.239 --> 00:31:36.283
Jabu is as naughty
as always.


579
00:31:36.366 --> 00:31:38.535
But everyone's fine,
Mama.


580
00:31:38.619 --> 00:31:41.455
Mama,
I need some money.


581
00:31:41.538 --> 00:31:44.291
Lindiwe has to
have new shoes.


582
00:31:44.374 --> 00:31:46.168
They split.

583
00:31:46.251 --> 00:31:49.671
They're no good.

584
00:31:49.755 --> 00:31:51.632
Have the Boers gone away?

585
00:31:51.715 --> 00:31:55.510
Yes.
Just for the afternoon.


586
00:31:55.594 --> 00:31:57.846
How much money
do you want?


587
00:31:57.929 --> 00:31:59.723
Sarafina!

588
00:31:59.806 --> 00:32:02.476
Sarafina!

589
00:32:02.559 --> 00:32:04.519
Where do you think
you are going?


590
00:32:04.603 --> 00:32:06.063
Sarafina!

591
00:32:06.146 --> 00:32:08.231
Sarafina,
come back here!


592
00:32:08.315 --> 00:32:11.526
A little refreshment,
Mrs. Vandermoever.


593
00:32:11.610 --> 00:32:13.695
The maid
will take your coat.


594
00:32:13.779 --> 00:32:16.573
Gin, brandy, rum?

595
00:32:16.657 --> 00:32:18.533
Or perhaps you would
like the maid


596
00:32:18.617 --> 00:32:21.620
to mix you
a refreshing lemonade?


597
00:32:21.703 --> 00:32:24.247
Do sit down,
Mrs. Vandermoever.


598
00:32:24.331 --> 00:32:27.542
You walked all the way
from the front gate


599
00:32:27.626 --> 00:32:29.503
on your own legs.

600
00:32:29.586 --> 00:32:32.381
Huh! You must be exhausted.

601
00:32:32.464 --> 00:32:35.217
Next time,
you wait by the gate,


602
00:32:35.300 --> 00:32:37.052
and the maid
will carry you.


603
00:32:37.135 --> 00:32:38.887
No problem, my dear.

604
00:32:38.970 --> 00:32:41.390
These black women
are so strong.


605
00:32:41.473 --> 00:32:44.351
That's enough, Sarafina!

606
00:32:44.434 --> 00:32:47.396
Sometimes you're such
a naughty little girl.


607
00:32:48.814 --> 00:32:50.399
Sarafina!

608
00:32:50.482 --> 00:32:53.193
Sarafina, where
are you going now?


609
00:32:53.276 --> 00:32:55.195
( humming )

610
00:32:58.156 --> 00:32:59.408
Whoo!

611
00:33:03.036 --> 00:33:06.331
Get off that bed,
you silly girl!


612
00:33:07.999 --> 00:33:12.421
Sarafina,
come back here!


613
00:33:12.504 --> 00:33:14.297
What's the matter
with you anyway?


614
00:33:14.381 --> 00:33:15.674
Have you gone crazy?

615
00:33:15.757 --> 00:33:16.967
Yes, I've gone crazy.

616
00:33:17.050 --> 00:33:18.427
You want me
to lose my job?


617
00:33:18.510 --> 00:33:19.886
Yes.

618
00:33:19.970 --> 00:33:21.388
And who's gonna buy
your school books?


619
00:33:21.471 --> 00:33:23.765
School books
are full of lies.


620
00:33:31.022 --> 00:33:33.316
You're a stupid girl,
Sarafina.


621
00:33:33.400 --> 00:33:35.569
Get off that bed
and show some sense.


622
00:33:35.652 --> 00:33:36.945
I want to kill them.

623
00:33:37.028 --> 00:33:38.947
Kill them? What for?

624
00:33:39.030 --> 00:33:40.741
They are good people.

625
00:33:40.824 --> 00:33:43.827
You've been a servant
for too long, Mama.


626
00:33:43.910 --> 00:33:46.955
Maybe that's because
your papa's been dead too long.


627
00:33:47.038 --> 00:33:49.124
Papa died fighting.

628
00:33:49.207 --> 00:33:50.459
He did not die fighting.

629
00:33:50.542 --> 00:33:52.836
He got sick in Mozambique,
and he died.


630
00:33:52.919 --> 00:33:54.463
He died for the struggle.

631
00:33:54.546 --> 00:33:57.340
Oh, sure. He went away
to be a hero,


632
00:33:57.424 --> 00:34:00.302
and I stayed home to work.

633
00:34:00.385 --> 00:34:02.345
Don't talk like that.

634
00:34:02.429 --> 00:34:04.973
I've got four children
and no man.


635
00:34:05.056 --> 00:34:07.434
My children
cannot eat glory.


636
00:34:07.517 --> 00:34:09.478
We eat servant food.

637
00:34:09.561 --> 00:34:11.646
Food is food.
You want to starve?


638
00:34:12.898 --> 00:34:14.483
Maybe.

639
00:34:14.566 --> 00:34:15.984
The way you're going on,

640
00:34:16.067 --> 00:34:18.487
you just might end up
dead like your papa.


641
00:34:18.570 --> 00:34:21.740
I'd rather die like him
than live like you.


642
00:34:23.784 --> 00:34:26.578
I've got work to do.

643
00:34:32.918 --> 00:34:35.086
( man shouting,
boy screaming )


644
00:34:38.298 --> 00:34:40.550
( indistinct shouting
and screaming )


645
00:34:44.429 --> 00:34:46.556
( laughs )

646
00:34:46.640 --> 00:34:48.016
I'm not your brother, okay?

647
00:34:48.099 --> 00:34:49.851
I'm not your brother.

648
00:34:49.935 --> 00:34:51.561
( screaming )

649
00:34:51.645 --> 00:34:54.523
Eh, who's paying you?
I'm not your brother!


650
00:34:54.606 --> 00:34:57.234
I'm not your brother!

651
00:34:57.317 --> 00:34:59.027
MAN: Sabela!

652
00:34:57.317 --> 00:34:59.027
Yes, sir!

653
00:34:59.110 --> 00:35:00.403
Give him Prince.

654
00:35:00.487 --> 00:35:01.863
Thank you, sir.

655
00:35:01.947 --> 00:35:04.407
( boy screaming )

656
00:35:06.409 --> 00:35:08.370
( dog barking )

657
00:35:08.453 --> 00:35:09.830
Sic 'im! Sic 'im!

658
00:35:09.913 --> 00:35:11.206
Go, Prince!

659
00:35:11.289 --> 00:35:13.708
( dog barking )

660
00:35:13.792 --> 00:35:16.169
( men laughing )

661
00:35:20.257 --> 00:35:21.675
( dog growling )

662
00:35:21.758 --> 00:35:26.346
( screaming )

663
00:35:26.429 --> 00:35:29.724
Go on! Go on!

664
00:35:29.808 --> 00:35:30.934
Aah! Aah!

665
00:35:31.017 --> 00:35:32.936
Aah! Aah!

666
00:35:33.019 --> 00:35:35.605
( dog barking )

667
00:35:35.689 --> 00:35:36.898
( shouting
in native language )


668
00:35:36.982 --> 00:35:39.401
Ha, ha, ha!

669
00:35:36.982 --> 00:35:39.401
( dog barking )

670
00:36:01.172 --> 00:36:02.883
( knocks on door )

671
00:36:04.175 --> 00:36:05.886
( knocking )

672
00:36:11.683 --> 00:36:13.810
Unh!

673
00:36:15.562 --> 00:36:18.273
It was Sabela.

674
00:36:18.356 --> 00:36:20.400
They set a dog on me.

675
00:36:20.483 --> 00:36:22.402
Our time will come.

676
00:36:22.485 --> 00:36:24.779
I'll kill him!

677
00:36:24.863 --> 00:36:26.781
And his bloody dog.

678
00:36:26.865 --> 00:36:28.742
No need for killing.

679
00:36:28.825 --> 00:36:30.619
When the people rise up,

680
00:36:30.702 --> 00:36:32.787
you'll see him
singing a new song...


681
00:36:32.871 --> 00:36:35.957
when they march down
commissioner street like a sea,


682
00:36:36.041 --> 00:36:39.628
Constable Sabela will shit
himself with fear,


683
00:36:39.711 --> 00:36:43.089
and up will go his fist.
"viva, Mandela, viva."


684
00:36:43.173 --> 00:36:46.468
Oh, man, I'd love
to see that.


685
00:36:46.551 --> 00:36:48.929
(<i>singing in native language</i> )

686
00:38:09.968 --> 00:38:12.345
( indistinct chatter )

687
00:38:24.482 --> 00:38:25.942
( man whistles )

688
00:38:30.488 --> 00:38:31.865
( wolf whistle )

689
00:38:31.948 --> 00:38:33.408
( knocking )

690
00:38:36.870 --> 00:38:39.873
( knocking )

691
00:38:45.503 --> 00:38:47.630
Miss Masembuko?

692
00:38:54.137 --> 00:38:56.431
Sarafina.

693
00:39:09.527 --> 00:39:11.112
Come in.

694
00:39:11.196 --> 00:39:12.614
Give me a moment, okay?

695
00:39:12.697 --> 00:39:14.532
Okay.

696
00:39:21.456 --> 00:39:25.126
( whispering )

697
00:39:30.215 --> 00:39:31.424
I love you.

698
00:39:31.508 --> 00:39:33.510
MARY:
I love you too.


699
00:39:37.555 --> 00:39:40.558
Ow! Ooh!

700
00:39:40.642 --> 00:39:41.810
Aah.

701
00:39:41.893 --> 00:39:43.686
All right.

702
00:39:43.770 --> 00:39:45.563
Please.
Okay. Okay.


703
00:40:04.374 --> 00:40:05.792
Next week?

704
00:40:05.875 --> 00:40:08.336
I love you too. Okay.

705
00:40:08.419 --> 00:40:12.215
Go, go.
Okay. Bye.


706
00:40:13.424 --> 00:40:15.135
Bye.

707
00:40:22.100 --> 00:40:23.351
What happened?

708
00:40:23.434 --> 00:40:24.602
The water spilled.

709
00:40:24.686 --> 00:40:26.229
Oh, leave it.
Give me.


710
00:40:26.312 --> 00:40:28.189
Sit down.

711
00:40:31.484 --> 00:40:33.570
So, Sarafina,

712
00:40:33.653 --> 00:40:35.613
what brings you here?

713
00:40:38.449 --> 00:40:39.993
Trouble at home?

714
00:40:43.121 --> 00:40:48.209
The boys...
they can fight.


715
00:40:48.293 --> 00:40:49.878
What can I do?

716
00:40:51.629 --> 00:40:53.756
There are other ways,
Sarafina.


717
00:40:53.840 --> 00:40:55.925
Like what?

718
00:40:56.009 --> 00:40:58.344
You know
what they say.


719
00:40:58.428 --> 00:41:00.930
If you want
to find a way,


720
00:41:01.014 --> 00:41:03.057
you must first know
where you're going.


721
00:41:03.141 --> 00:41:05.059
No way.

722
00:41:05.143 --> 00:41:07.228
That's not true.

723
00:41:07.312 --> 00:41:10.899
What do you want?

724
00:41:10.982 --> 00:41:14.194
What do you want,
mistress?


725
00:41:14.277 --> 00:41:15.862
Me?

726
00:41:15.945 --> 00:41:19.574
I want
very many things.


727
00:41:19.657 --> 00:41:22.869
I want the war
to be over.


728
00:41:22.952 --> 00:41:27.040
I want the hate
to be over.


729
00:41:27.123 --> 00:41:30.418
I want my Joe
back in my arms.


730
00:41:30.501 --> 00:41:36.257
I want quiet days
and loving nights.


731
00:41:36.341 --> 00:41:39.552
I want babies.

732
00:41:40.845 --> 00:41:43.848
I want to come home
to kindness.


733
00:42:10.375 --> 00:42:12.794
Would you believe me
if I told you


734
00:42:12.877 --> 00:42:14.879
this was not mine?

735
00:42:14.963 --> 00:42:16.965
Yes.

736
00:42:17.048 --> 00:42:20.468
I've never even held it
in my hands.


737
00:42:20.551 --> 00:42:23.263
It's Joe's.

738
00:42:23.346 --> 00:42:25.932
He uses it?

739
00:42:26.015 --> 00:42:29.269
He has done.

740
00:42:29.352 --> 00:42:32.939
I won't tell anyone.

741
00:42:33.022 --> 00:42:36.651
I meant what I said.

742
00:42:36.734 --> 00:42:38.319
I hate the killing.

743
00:42:38.403 --> 00:42:41.489
I hate the violence.

744
00:42:41.572 --> 00:42:43.449
But I cannot stand aside

745
00:42:43.533 --> 00:42:47.078
and let others die for me.

746
00:42:47.161 --> 00:42:50.623
I will fight too.

747
00:42:50.707 --> 00:42:53.543
I can't kill.

748
00:42:53.626 --> 00:42:56.254
Don't ask me to kill.

749
00:42:57.880 --> 00:43:00.466
It's the same
old argument.


750
00:43:00.550 --> 00:43:02.844
What if they
come for you...


751
00:43:02.927 --> 00:43:05.013
Come to the door...

752
00:43:05.096 --> 00:43:07.056
kick it in?

753
00:43:07.140 --> 00:43:09.392
Do you reach
for the gun?


754
00:43:09.475 --> 00:43:12.061
Do you shoot?

755
00:43:13.438 --> 00:43:16.357
Do I?

756
00:43:16.441 --> 00:43:18.693
I don't know.

757
00:43:22.280 --> 00:43:24.240
I don't know.

758
00:43:24.324 --> 00:43:26.909
( thunder rumbles
in the distance )


759
00:43:28.328 --> 00:43:30.496
( thunder )

760
00:43:41.132 --> 00:43:43.259
( thunder )

761
00:43:48.139 --> 00:43:50.558
( crashing )

762
00:43:52.268 --> 00:43:53.394
( children screaming )

763
00:43:53.478 --> 00:43:54.812
( yelling )

764
00:44:07.033 --> 00:44:10.119
( yelling continues )

765
00:44:20.213 --> 00:44:21.839
Get in. Get in!

766
00:44:21.923 --> 00:44:23.424
Get in there!
Oh, shut up,


767
00:44:23.508 --> 00:44:25.635
the rest of you!

768
00:44:25.718 --> 00:44:27.678
( helicopter hovering )

769
00:44:27.762 --> 00:44:29.889
( children crying )

770
00:44:34.185 --> 00:44:37.438
PRINCIPAL:
It's no more than rumors,
but in the present climate,


771
00:44:37.522 --> 00:44:39.607
we must listen
to everything.


772
00:44:39.690 --> 00:44:43.444
I've given Lieutenant Bloem
my firm opinion which is:


773
00:44:43.528 --> 00:44:45.405
you are
a responsible teacher


774
00:44:45.488 --> 00:44:47.615
who would do nothing
to harm the children.


775
00:44:47.698 --> 00:44:48.825
Am I right?

776
00:44:48.908 --> 00:44:51.160
Oh, yes, principal.

777
00:44:51.244 --> 00:44:53.913
Mary, do you teach
the children Communism?


778
00:44:53.996 --> 00:44:55.164
No, principal.

779
00:44:55.248 --> 00:44:57.291
Do you teach them
violent revolution?


780
00:44:57.375 --> 00:44:59.252
No, principal.

781
00:44:59.335 --> 00:45:01.963
Do you teach the authorized
syllabus, Miss Masembuko?


782
00:45:02.046 --> 00:45:03.464
Yes.

783
00:45:03.548 --> 00:45:05.466
With additional material
of your own?


784
00:45:05.550 --> 00:45:07.051
Yes.

785
00:45:05.550 --> 00:45:07.051
PRINCIPAL: Mary...

786
00:45:07.135 --> 00:45:09.011
you have to follow
the authorized syllabus.


787
00:45:09.095 --> 00:45:10.471
You know that.

788
00:45:10.555 --> 00:45:12.974
And what is this, um,
additional material?


789
00:45:13.057 --> 00:45:15.643
I want them to know
where they come from.


790
00:45:15.726 --> 00:45:18.396
I want them to have
a sense of pride in themselves.


791
00:45:18.479 --> 00:45:19.939
Black pride.

792
00:45:20.022 --> 00:45:22.316
If you will.

793
00:45:22.400 --> 00:45:24.694
You're playing with fire.

794
00:45:24.777 --> 00:45:27.155
Would you rather
they were ashamed of themselves?


795
00:45:27.238 --> 00:45:29.323
I'll tell you
what I'd rather.


796
00:45:29.407 --> 00:45:31.492
I'd rather they be left in peace
to go to school,


797
00:45:31.576 --> 00:45:33.786
get an education,
get a chance in life,


798
00:45:33.870 --> 00:45:35.663
not get their heads stuffed
with crazy dreams.


799
00:45:35.746 --> 00:45:38.458
Like maybe one day there
won't be police at the school?


800
00:45:38.541 --> 00:45:41.294
Like maybe one day we won't be
afraid of each other?


801
00:45:41.377 --> 00:45:44.338
PRINCIPAL:
Mary, you're a fine teacher.


802
00:45:44.422 --> 00:45:46.507
I don't want to lose you.

803
00:45:46.591 --> 00:45:49.802
Follow the authorized syllabus
from now on, please,


804
00:45:49.886 --> 00:45:51.220
and nothing else.

805
00:45:51.304 --> 00:45:53.514
Right, principal.

806
00:45:53.598 --> 00:45:57.852
PRINCIPAL:
