1140
01:12:30.193 --> 01:12:31.360
( speaks African language )

1141
01:12:46.709 --> 01:12:48.795
( door slams shut )

1142
01:12:48.878 --> 01:12:50.797
MAN:
Do you go to school?


1143
01:12:50.880 --> 01:12:52.632
Yes.

1144
01:12:52.715 --> 01:12:55.510
So why aren't you
in school?


1145
01:12:57.845 --> 01:12:59.639
Why aren't you
in school?


1146
01:12:59.722 --> 01:13:02.517
Because of the soldiers.

1147
01:13:04.393 --> 01:13:07.480
Soldiers don't stop you
from studying.


1148
01:13:10.233 --> 01:13:12.443
Answer my questions, ma'am.

1149
01:13:12.527 --> 01:13:15.071
You didn't ask
a question.


1150
01:13:18.074 --> 01:13:20.952
How do the soldiers
stop you from studying?


1151
01:13:22.703 --> 01:13:24.330
By killing us.

1152
01:13:26.374 --> 01:13:28.543
You're not dead.

1153
01:13:28.626 --> 01:13:30.503
Are you dead?

1154
01:13:30.586 --> 01:13:32.171
No.

1155
01:13:32.255 --> 01:13:34.841
So why aren't you
in school?


1156
01:13:34.924 --> 01:13:36.801
My friends are dead.

1157
01:13:36.884 --> 01:13:38.427
Your friends?

1158
01:13:41.639 --> 01:13:45.268
The students who attacked
the soldiers are your friends?


1159
01:13:47.103 --> 01:13:49.522
Students who murdered
a constable last night,


1160
01:13:49.605 --> 01:13:51.065
they're your friends?

1161
01:13:52.775 --> 01:13:55.361
Is that how
your friends behave...


1162
01:13:55.444 --> 01:13:56.779
like wild animals?

1163
01:13:58.447 --> 01:14:00.867
Where were you
last night?


1164
01:14:00.950 --> 01:14:03.369
At home.

1165
01:14:03.452 --> 01:14:08.875
Do you know how
Constable Sabela was murdered?


1166
01:14:08.958 --> 01:14:12.044
A mob of children
burned him to death.


1167
01:14:12.128 --> 01:14:13.880
Did you know that?

1168
01:14:13.963 --> 01:14:16.048
I heard.

1169
01:14:16.132 --> 01:14:18.342
So, what do you
think about it?


1170
01:14:20.011 --> 01:14:21.679
Nothing.

1171
01:14:21.762 --> 01:14:23.848
Nothing.

1172
01:14:25.808 --> 01:14:27.560
Do you think...

1173
01:14:27.643 --> 01:14:31.647
burning a man to death
is nothing?


1174
01:14:31.731 --> 01:14:33.024
Hey!

1175
01:14:36.444 --> 01:14:38.487
What's going on
in the schools, huh?


1176
01:14:41.157 --> 01:14:43.868
Somebody's looking
for trouble, aren't they?


1177
01:14:46.287 --> 01:14:48.748
Are you looking for trouble?

1178
01:14:50.500 --> 01:14:51.792
You don't have
to look for trouble.


1179
01:14:51.876 --> 01:14:53.085
What's that?

1180
01:14:53.169 --> 01:14:57.590
We don't have
to look for trouble.


1181
01:14:57.673 --> 01:15:00.927
Trouble finds you, huh?

1182
01:15:01.010 --> 01:15:04.013
Our life is trouble.

1183
01:15:04.096 --> 01:15:06.182
So whose fault is that?

1184
01:15:07.892 --> 01:15:09.268
Who's making the trouble?

1185
01:15:11.354 --> 01:15:14.649
We're not completely
stupid, you know.


1186
01:15:14.732 --> 01:15:18.069
School kids don't just
come up with this stuff


1187
01:15:18.152 --> 01:15:20.947
out of their own heads.

1188
01:15:21.030 --> 01:15:23.282
We know
you're being used.


1189
01:15:25.284 --> 01:15:28.371
Do you know
Mary Masembuko?


1190
01:15:28.454 --> 01:15:30.289
She's my teacher.

1191
01:15:30.373 --> 01:15:31.999
Was.

1192
01:15:35.586 --> 01:15:37.588
What do you mean?

1193
01:15:39.048 --> 01:15:40.633
She killed herself.

1194
01:15:44.387 --> 01:15:46.389
Did you ever go
to her house?


1195
01:15:48.266 --> 01:15:51.894
Did you ever meet
Joe Masembuko?


1196
01:15:54.021 --> 01:15:57.400
How did she die?

1197
01:15:57.483 --> 01:16:00.152
She jumped out
the window.


1198
01:16:00.236 --> 01:16:02.363
Tenth floor.

1199
01:16:03.572 --> 01:16:06.033
You didn't have to kill her.

1200
01:16:06.117 --> 01:16:08.995
I told you, she killed herself.

1201
01:16:09.078 --> 01:16:10.454
She wanted to die.

1202
01:16:10.538 --> 01:16:13.541
No.

1203
01:16:13.624 --> 01:16:15.668
I knew her.

1204
01:16:15.751 --> 01:16:17.878
She wanted...

1205
01:16:19.588 --> 01:16:21.716
She wanted so much.

1206
01:16:23.592 --> 01:16:27.430
So you knew her
pretty well, huh?


1207
01:16:30.766 --> 01:16:33.102
I loved her.

1208
01:16:35.271 --> 01:16:40.359
Yeah. So you can
help me, can't you?


1209
01:16:44.780 --> 01:16:47.199
Did you meet anyone else
at her house?


1210
01:16:52.788 --> 01:16:54.373
All right.

1211
01:16:57.126 --> 01:16:58.878
Now you listen to me, girlie,

1212
01:16:58.961 --> 01:17:01.630
and you listen hard.

1213
01:17:01.714 --> 01:17:04.675
I don't give a shit
how young you are.


1214
01:17:04.759 --> 01:17:06.385
You throw a bomb at me,

1215
01:17:06.469 --> 01:17:08.346
I'm gonna kill you.

1216
01:17:08.429 --> 01:17:11.015
You try to burn down my house,

1217
01:17:11.098 --> 01:17:13.309
I'm gonna kill you.

1218
01:17:13.392 --> 01:17:17.396
You make war on<i>my</i> country,

1219
01:17:17.480 --> 01:17:18.981
I'm gonna kill you.

1220
01:17:22.193 --> 01:17:24.070
You think you got
the whole of black Africa


1221
01:17:24.153 --> 01:17:26.739
just waiting
to roll on over us, eh?


1222
01:17:26.822 --> 01:17:28.908
You try it.

1223
01:17:28.991 --> 01:17:30.201
Just try it.

1224
01:17:30.284 --> 01:17:32.453
We're ready for you.

1225
01:17:35.247 --> 01:17:36.874
So...

1226
01:17:36.957 --> 01:17:39.502
let's just stop
horsing around, eh?


1227
01:17:44.673 --> 01:17:46.759
Tenth floor.

1228
01:17:46.842 --> 01:17:48.010
( door slams shut )

1229
01:17:49.387 --> 01:17:51.555
SARAFINA:
<i>I killed a man, Nelson.</i>


1230
01:17:51.639 --> 01:17:53.599
<i>Is that what you want?</i>

1231
01:17:53.682 --> 01:17:55.476
<i>Did</i> I<i>kill him?</i>

1232
01:17:55.559 --> 01:17:59.105
<i>I was there.</i>
<i>I wanted to kill him.</i>


1233
01:17:59.188 --> 01:18:00.981
<i>I saw his eyes.</i>

1234
01:18:01.065 --> 01:18:04.485
<i>I hated him so much,</i>
<i>I wanted to kill him.</i>


1235
01:18:04.568 --> 01:18:06.987
<i>But then I saw his eyes.</i>

1236
01:18:07.071 --> 01:18:10.116
<i>See what they've done</i>
<i>to me, Nelson?</i>


1237
01:18:10.199 --> 01:18:13.994
<i>They've filled me up with hate,</i>
<i>but not enough.</i>


1238
01:18:14.078 --> 01:18:16.497
<i>I have to be</i>
<i>so full of hate,</i>


1239
01:18:16.580 --> 01:18:19.250
<i>there's no room</i>
<i>for anything else.</i>


1240
01:18:19.333 --> 01:18:21.627
Make me numb, Nelson.

1241
01:18:21.710 --> 01:18:23.796
Make me numb.

1242
01:18:26.006 --> 01:18:28.551
( woman screams )

1243
01:18:34.432 --> 01:18:36.892
You're not there, are you?

1244
01:18:39.061 --> 01:18:41.230
You can't hear me.

1245
01:18:43.232 --> 01:18:45.109
You can't hear anyone.

1246
01:18:45.192 --> 01:18:48.320
You've gone away.

1247
01:18:48.404 --> 01:18:50.239
We just dreamed you.

1248
01:18:52.116 --> 01:18:55.161
You've been away
too long, Nelson.


1249
01:18:55.244 --> 01:18:57.830
You're old now,

1250
01:18:57.913 --> 01:19:00.833
and your children are dying,

1251
01:19:00.916 --> 01:19:03.836
and you can't hear us.

1252
01:19:03.919 --> 01:19:05.880
( "Safa Saphel' Isizwe"
<i>playing</i> )


1253
01:19:08.591 --> 01:19:10.885
(<i>chorus singing</i>
<i>in native language</i> )


1254
01:20:04.063 --> 01:20:08.400
They took me to a prison,
and they beat me.


1255
01:20:08.484 --> 01:20:09.818
When I cried,

1256
01:20:09.902 --> 01:20:11.737
they put their biggest gun
in my mouth


1257
01:20:11.820 --> 01:20:13.906
so I wouldn't cry.

1258
01:20:13.989 --> 01:20:16.450
Then they covered my head
with a wet sack


1259
01:20:16.534 --> 01:20:19.578
and gave me the electricity.

1260
01:20:19.662 --> 01:20:23.874
I cried like a little babe
holding the gun in my mouth.


1261
01:20:25.209 --> 01:20:27.419
GIRL:
<i>He took me to a room</i>


1262
01:20:27.503 --> 01:20:30.923
<i>full of dead bodies.</i>

1263
01:20:31.006 --> 01:20:34.093
<i>He said he would</i>
<i>leave me with them.</i>


1264
01:20:34.176 --> 01:20:37.721
I began to cry.

1265
01:20:37.805 --> 01:20:41.600
He took my face,
then turned it to the light...


1266
01:20:41.684 --> 01:20:43.936
and he laughed.

1267
01:20:44.019 --> 01:20:45.729
And he said,

1268
01:20:45.813 --> 01:20:48.941
"Look, your eyes are pissing."

1269
01:21:02.329 --> 01:21:03.581
GUARD:
Come on.


1270
01:21:18.887 --> 01:21:21.849
BOY:
<i>He shouted my name.</i>


1271
01:21:21.932 --> 01:21:23.809
<i>He pointed at me.</i>

1272
01:21:23.893 --> 01:21:25.811
<i>"Come to me, boy."</i>

1273
01:21:25.894 --> 01:21:30.190
I was so afraid
I couldn't speak.


1274
01:21:30.274 --> 01:21:33.819
I walked slowly towards him.

1275
01:21:33.902 --> 01:21:35.654
When I was close,

1276
01:21:35.738 --> 01:21:38.490
he hit me hard, here.

1277
01:21:38.574 --> 01:21:40.492
It hurt so much

1278
01:21:40.576 --> 01:21:44.330
I screamed
and fell to the ground.


1279
01:21:44.413 --> 01:21:47.458
He pointed at me again.

1280
01:21:47.541 --> 01:21:49.668
"Come to me, boy."

1281
01:21:49.752 --> 01:21:54.798
I was still crying.
I knew he would hit me again.


1282
01:21:54.882 --> 01:21:56.675
I put my hands here

1283
01:21:56.759 --> 01:21:59.219
so it wouldn't hurt so bad,

1284
01:21:59.303 --> 01:22:01.347
but he hit me again.

1285
01:22:01.430 --> 01:22:06.352
It hurt so bad
I couldn't cry anymore.


1286
01:22:06.435 --> 01:22:11.649
There were many of us,
all from my school.


1287
01:22:11.732 --> 01:22:14.318
They took us to a big room.

1288
01:22:14.401 --> 01:22:17.696
<i>They told us</i>
<i>to take off our clothes,</i>


1289
01:22:17.780 --> 01:22:20.824
<i>all our clothes.</i>

1290
01:22:20.908 --> 01:22:23.869
<i>They told us</i>
